title: The SAP Sapphire AI preview - seven burning questions about AI that SAP should address
description: There's no way around it: SAP is going to have some things to say about AI at SAP Sapphire. So let's sharpen our questions also, with seven hot AI topics to track in Orlando. I've also included a key AI issue from three notable SAP user groups: ASUG, DSAG, and UKISUG.

title: It’s time to bring tax into the real-time era
description: Legacy tax processes can’t keep pace with digital mandates. Richard Jones of Confluent explains how real-time data streaming offers a smarter path to compliance and control.

title: Resilient digital twins - essential in the age of AI and automation
description: Simple Digital Twins of an Organization (DTOs) are not enough in today’s turbulent times, says Celonis’ chief scientist Wil van der Aalst. He outlines the key steps for implementing and maintaining a resilient digital twin and why it is critical to ensuring AI has the data it needs to succeed.

title: 93% of IT execs are eager to implement agentic AI – but have they considered governance?
description: AI agents are helping enterprises automate complex workflows, but success depends on thoughtful design and governance. Cameron Mehin of UiPath shares why controlled agency is key to balancing autonomy with oversight.
